   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1: NAP formulated and communicated based on identified CCA priorities and in close coordination with plans already in place
2: Standards and a protocol established to track CCA project financing and investments</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2018">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1: NAP process begun with NAP roadmap, but NAP document has not been drafted and implementation workplan and communications strategy are not in place. (2018)
2: A climate fiscal framework was established in 2014 but is no longer operational. Standards and protocols with comprehensive functional tracking mechanisms for climate finance do not exist. (2018)</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2022-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2022-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Synthesis report on climate risk and vulnerability, gap analysis report of climate change mainstreaming in planning and budgeting systems across government and capacity needs assessment report to steer the NAP process at the national level, proposed institutional framework and coordination mechanism, national NAP mandate drafted, CCIKM portal, climate vulnerability scenarios available for several prioritized sector, synopsis on valuation of economic impacts
2. Final Draft NAP document
3.Draft capacity building action plan on CC, integration of CCA in 5-year development plan, developed climate risk screening tools, developed racking indicators for IMWG and at NDA, MoEFCC
4. Adaptation finance tracking mechanism incorporated into the CCIKM portal, costed NAP document, analysis of CCA financing options</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Developed institutional coordination and climate change (CC) information and knowledge management (CCIKM) for medium- to long-term planning.
2. Adaptation options appraised and prioritized, and the National Adaptation Plan formulated including peer and public review processes, implementation work plan and M&amp;E plan in place, and communications strategy and outreach plan in place.
3. Climate risk-informed decision-making tools developed to piloted by planning and budget departments at national and sectoral levels.
4. Adaptation finance tracking mechanism adopted, CCA actions within NAP costed, comprehensive analysis of options for CCA financing conducted and financing sources public and private &#x2013;international and domestic options identified for priority sectors and in priority regions of the country.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Developed NAP zero draft 
2. Structure and architecture of CCIKM web-portal developed</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. NAP zero draft developed but not yet validated and reviewed 
2. Structure and architecture of CCIKM web-portal developed but not yet operational</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
